# ElimuPath Environment Configuration

## Production Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` in the production environment.

```env
# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://db_user:db_password@db_host:5432/elimupath_prod

# Server
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production
FRONTEND_URL=https://elimupath.com

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=generate_a_long_random_string_here

# Redis
REDIS_URL=redis://redis_host:6379

# Storage (Future-proof)
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=
S3_BUCKET_NAME=
```

## Security Recommendations
- Use a strong, unique `JWT_SECRET`.
- Ensure `DATABASE_URL` uses an encrypted connection (SSL/TLS).
- Set `NODE_ENV` to `production` to enable Express optimizations.
- Verify that `FRONTEND_URL` exactly matches the domain serving your React app.
